cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is about object recognition and transfer learning using pre-trained CNNs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the optimization of network architecture, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of soft-attention mechanisms and complexity regularization constraints also suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses character and traffic sign recognition, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
